name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Community Red
New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Grey

details.description:
The New Balance 990v6 Grey is another recent addition to the New Balance brand´s running catalog.

This 990v6 model in a grey color scheme features an upper mesh base with premium suede overlays. Branding elements are scattered throughout; for example, the V6 is noted in red on the tongue. The shoe features a sole unit underfoot with a contoured midsole. Its heels feature a series of curves and lines and a rubber outsole at the base. The sole utilizes ABZORB cushioning pluse Fuel Cell and ENCAP technology.

The New Balance 990v6 Grey was released on November 4th, 2022, at a retail price of $200.

DISCLAIMER: There are two versions of this shoe with the same style ID but they have a slight variation on the heel. The first version is shown in our product imagery and includes a New Balance NB logo on the heel. The second version has an American flag in. Both versions are acceptable for sellers to sell and buyers could receive either version in their order.

name: New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Grey Silver

details.description:
The New Balance 990v4 Made in USA Grey Silver is a part of the 990 series, which is well-known for its quality, comfort, and timeless aesthetic.

The New Balance 990v4 Grey Silver comes with an upper in different tones of Grey. With an upper crafted from a combination of premium pigskin suede and breathable mesh, it is durable, ventilated, and flexible, allowing for a wide range of movement. The mesh and suede parts come in a light grey colorway, and details of darker grey outline the mesh parts. The iconic " N" logo on the side of the shoe follows the same grey colorway. And ENCAP midsole technology provides a superior level of support and cushioning with its dual-density foam system.

But what our experts love most about the New Balance 990v4 Made in USA Grey Silver is the ABZORB technology set in the midsole to absorb shocks and reduce the impact of your steps. These shoes have been keeping feet stylish and comfortable since their release on June 2, 2023, for a price of $185.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson Ainôzama
New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Workwear Grey

details.description:
The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Workwear Grey updates the running shoe technology introduced in the 990 and designs a high-performance running shoe that is as stylish as it is dependable.

The Made in USA New Balance 990 v6 in a Workwear/Grey colorway begins with an upper base of tannish-orange mesh that offers lightweight breathability. Perforated dark-gray leather forms overlays that course across the upper, tannish-orange suede forms the overlays at the eyestays and mud guard, and silvery leather hits the upper at the collar. The gray and white ENCAP midsole is made with propulsive FuelCell foam that offers cushioning and energy return and a polyurethane rim that provides durability. This sneaker rides on a black and gray rubber outsole.

Our favorite feature of this sneaker is the design of the side panel N, which features horizontally corrugated silvery-gray synthetic that is also used in the upper eyestays. The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Workwear Grey was released on March 4, 2024, for $200 retail.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White

details.description:
The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White continues to deliver the original New Balance 990 goal of a perfect running shoe by combining FuelCell technology on the midsole and a fabric lining in grey tones.

The body of the New Balance 990v6 has a mesh underlay in a black hue. A dark suede overlay starts on the mudguard and proceeds to cover the circumference of the border between the shoe and the sole. On the quarter panels, a mix of mesh base, black suede, grey synthetic strips, and the "N" New Balance branding in light grey are present. A similar overlay design appears on the heel.

StockX experts think the colorful logos distributed on this shoe’s surface make it stand out and give it an identity. A red V6 branding appears on the tongue alongside New Balance 990 embossed writing. Additionally, the NB logo with a Made in USA tag adorns the heel counter. Released on April 7th, 2023, the New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White had a retail price of $200.

name: New Balance 990v6 Triple Black

details.description:
The New Balance 990v6 Triple Black decks out the sixth version of the NB 990 in an all-black colorway and a mixed-material upper.

Launched to celebrate the 40th anniversary of the 990, the 990v6 boasts a sculpted midsole with ENCAP and FuelCell foam cushioning underfoot. The inclusion of FuelCell technology represents the latest evolution of the iconic 990 and helps propel the runner forward. The "Triple Black" colorway allows the sneaker’s technical upgrades to take center stage without distracting colors or motifs. In addition, the deep black hue makes the suede mudguard appear even more velvety against the mesh underlays.

Our experts like the reflective accents, which provide visibility in low lighting, and the metallic silver detailing on the heel and insole because they shine when compared to the "Triple Black" colorway. The New Balance 990v6 Triple Black was released on April 16, 2024, and sold for $199.

name: New Balance 990v5 Grey

details.description:
The New Balance 990v5 Grey is the fifth iteration of New Balance's iconic 990 series that originated in 1982. The 990v5 Grey arrives in NB's signature grey color scheme. Its upper is constructed of a grey mesh with matching suede overlays and translucent TPU side panels. Reflective detailing on the New Balance logo and piping shine when exposed to light. At the base, an ENCAP midsole offers utmost cushioning and support. This model is made in the United States of America.

The New Balance 990v5 released in February of 2019 and retailed for $175.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson Untitled
New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Grey Black Cream

details.description:
The New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Grey Black Cream is a version that pays homage to the original design of the running shoe.

This iteration of the New Balance 990v4 is constructed with a white textile upper for comfort and flexibility. White dominates the midsole and toe box while black and gray leather overlays round out the toe box and cross the midsole from the arches to the laces. The New Balance signature "N" appears on the midsole in white outlined in black on top of the gray overlay. The heel collar is darker gray and contains an NB logo at the top, while the black heel counter contains the New Balance brand name. A branded off-white rubber outsole completes the look, and the midsole contains ENCAP cushioning.

What stands out about this shoe is the sleek design of the white textile and leather overlays. The muted design makes the shoe versatile. The New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Grey Black Cream was released on February 8, 2024, for a price of $200.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Teddy Santis Light Mushroom Moonrock
New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Teddy Santis Reflection Marblehead

details.description:
The MiUSA Teddy Santis Reflection Marblehead New Balance 990v6 highlights premium materials and thoughtful design, giving you a harmonious mix of suede, mesh, and reflective aspects. As part of Teddy Santis' Made in USA series, these shoes are here to give the iconic 990v6 silhouette a slight facelift.

The MiUSA Teddy Santis Reflection Marblehead 990v6 by New Balance comes with a tonal grey suede upper paired with breathable underlays, giving you a layered look and improving the airflow. The reflective detailing on the "N" logo is for visibility. This design incorporates New Balance’s ENCAP midsole technology and blends foam with a polyurethane rim to strengthen them. The "Made in USA" line reflects New Balance’s commitment to American-made products.

What we love about the MiUSA Teddy Santis Reflection Marblehead New Balance 990v6 is its reflective detailing, which improves safety and visual appeal, and the ENCAP midsole for a balance of cushioning and support. Released on 15th August 2024, it retailed at $220.

name: New Balance 990v3 MiUSA Grey

details.description:
The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 is one of the 2019 releases by shoe manufacturer New Balance.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 comes in grey and features a leather upper section. The upper part is also made of mesh patches in grey. In addition, the shoe has an ENCAP midsole cushioning with a lightweight foam combined with a rim made of durable polyurethane. The shoe also has white laces for a secure fit and the New Balance logo on both sides.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 was released on 1st October 2019 to retail at $165.

name: New Balance 990v3 MiUSA Bodega Here To Stay

details.description:
To celebrate 15 years of business, Boston-based boutique Bodega collaborated with New Balance on the 990v3. The two brands are no strangers to working together, and their last collaborative effort was on the 997S in 2020.

The New Balance 990v3 Bodega Here To Stay was inspired by the idea of preservation and people’s need to be remembered. Neutral tones make up the majority of the sneaker, with a cream ENCAP midsole and brown suede and beige leather overlays. Bodega’s logo is printed in bright crimson on the heel tab, while "2006" and "2021" are embroidered on the heel cap to commemorate the store’s 15-year anniversary.

The New Balance 990v3 Bodega Here To Stay released in June of 2021 for $220.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA True Camo White
New Balance 990v2 MiUSA Teddy Santis Marblehead Incense

details.description:
As part of Teddy Santis' New Balance Made In USA Spring 2022 collection, the New Balance 990v2 MIUSA Marblehead Incense features a brown mesh upper with grey and beige suede overlays and a reflective New Balance side logo. From there, an ABZORB sole provides cushioning and responsiveness.

The New Balance 990v2 MIUSA Marblehead Incense released in April of 2022 and retailed for $195.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Cream

details.description:
The New Balance 990 series is known for its premium craftsmanship, comfort, and versatility. The "v6" in the model’s name indicates that it is the sixth version in the series. The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Cream features high-quality materials in its construction, including a combination of suede, mesh, and leather. The use of premium materials contributes to the durability and overall quality of the shoe.

This New Balance model in MiUSA Cream has a color palette that is primarily composed of neutral shades, including yellow, white, taupe, gray, and light brown. New Balance's ENCAP technology is incorporated into the midsole, providing a balance of cushioning and support. The design of the 990v6 maintains the classic aesthetic that has been a hallmark of the 990 series. It's known for its clean lines, iconic "N" logo on the sides, and a versatile silhouette.

One feature that our experts love about the New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Cream is its comfortable cushioning, making it suitable for both casual wear and light athletic activities. It was released on July 7th, 2023, for $220.

name: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson Lapis Lazuli

details.description:
The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson Lapis Lazuli is a collaboratively designed sneaker release from New Balance and rapper Action Bronson. This shoe is part of the New Balance 990 line, which has been around since 1982.

The 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson in Lapis Lazuli has an Eclipse and Popcorn colorway and features New Balance branding on both sides. The sneaker has a dual-density foam midsole that is a combination of a softer foam layer at the top and a firmer layer at the bottom, which provides a balance of soft comfort and firm support.

We especially love the New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Action Bronson Lapis Lazuli for its craftsmanship. The use of suede from the toe box to the heel provides extra protection and reinforcement for the areas that see the most wear and tear. A large portion of the upper is also made from mesh, which allows air to circulate within the shoe and keep the foot cool and dry. The sneaker debuted on June 22nd, 2023, and retailed for $220.

name: New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Arctic Grey Black

details.description:
The New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Arctic Grey Black is a shoe designed in collaboration with designer and creative director Teddy Santis.

This version of the New Balance XX 990v4 is made with a mesh upper in Arctic Grey. Mesh takes up the toe box and the midsoles as well as the area around the ankle. Natural suede overlays in a darker gray color round out the toe box and cross the rest of the upper from the arch to the laces. The New Balance "N" appears on both sides of the shoe on top of the gray overlay in black. The heel counter is a light gray color and is branded with "990" on the lateral side. A Red NB adorns the back of the heel, while the New Balance brand name appears on the plastic support above the sole. A thick black rubber outsole completes the look.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the smooth gray colorway, which gives the shoe versatility and is easy on the eye. The New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Teddy Santis Arctic Grey Black was released on March 28, 2024, for a price of $210.
